			"Liquides Imaginaires is a French fragrance house founded by David Frossard and Philippe Di Méo.\nLiquides Imaginaires was created with an aim to revive the perfume ceremony and ritual by developing new objects and alternative habits. The bottles for Liquides Imaginaires' fragrances are designed to be mysterious and enclosing the genius of perfume within, like an amphora, as well as exceptional and precious objects made with the expertise of craftsmen. The fragrances themselves are like puzzles, to be used used to interpret thoughts, intentions, confessions; to commemorate passages of life, desires, beliefs, strengths and weaknesses; to help those who wear them leave the material world and cross into imaginary, intimate worlds, where the spirit scatters to explore other horizons and new desires.\nLiquides Imaginaires always release fragrances as a trilogy—a collection of three scents related in theme. The house also produces candles.\nDesigner Les Liquides Imaginaires has 21 perfumes in our fragrance base. Les Liquides Imaginaires is a new fragrance brand. The earliest edition was created in 2011 and the newest is from 2019. Les Liquides Imaginaires fragrances were made in collaboration with perfumers Louise Turner, Sonia Constant, Jórdi Fernandez, Amelie Bourgeois, Quentin Bisch, Nisrine Bouazzaoui Grillie, Shyamala Maisondieu, Nadege Le Garlantezec, Carine Bouin and Anne-Sophie Behaghel.",
