		title: "Memo Paris",
		description:
			"Memo Paris is a fragrance house founded by John and Clara Molloy in 2007. The pair met on a chair lift and decided to set off on a journey together. John Molloy grew up in the Irish countryside. Clara grew up in Andalusia. Both had a lifelong love of travel and adventure that inspired the collection of fragrances that would become Memo Paris.\nMemo Paris was named after Clara's memories collected from various parts of the world. As Clara says, she has tons of materials from her travels and those materials are her endless inspiration: Metro tickets, historical books, travel diaries ...\nIn conjunction with perfumer Alienor Massenet, Memo Paris has produced three EDP collections at this time, along with home scents, bath products and bespoke perfume services. Clara is also a fragrance writer and publisher and Memo Paris has published three volumes related to the fragrance industry.\nMemo Paris products are available at Colette and Le Bon Marché in Paris, Harvey Nichols Knightsbridge store in London, Bergdorf Goodman in the United States and select boutiques in 22 countries worldwide.\nDesigner Memo Paris has 41 perfumes in our fragrance base. The earliest edition was created in 2007 and the newest is from 2020. Memo Paris fragrances were made in collaboration with perfumers Alienor Massenet and Sophie Labbe.",
