		title: "Montana",
		description:
			"Montana Parfums is a relatively young France-based perfume house that launched their first fragrance Parfum de Peau which is composed of powerful, animalic and leathery notes in 1986. In 1989 the first fragrance for men was introduced. The composition of Montana Parfum d'Homme was built around leather, aldehydes, spices, patchouli, oak moss and floral notes. The second women's fragrance Parfum d'Elle with chypre and fruity notes was presented in 1990.\nIn 1994 the brand presented the floral perfumes Suggestion Eau d'Or and Suggestion Eau d'Argent which were both made for women. The sweet composition of Just Me with dominant notes of pineapple, honey and chocolate was created by Francoice Caron and launched in 1998. In 2000 the house of Montana released the floral-aquatic fragrance Montana Blue.\nMontana Homme was introduced in 2001 as a woody chypre follow-up on the first men's fragrance from 1989. In 2003 another men's fragrance was presented. The name of this green aromatic fougère fragrance is Montana Green. Parfum d'Elle 2 was launched in the same year as a fruity-floral edition of the orginal Parfum d'Elle from 1986.\nDriven by the success of the previously launched fragrances for both genders the house of Montana presented Malaita, a floral-aquatic composition, Samar, an oriental-floral scent with prominent floral notes and Suggestion Eau Cuivrée, a strong floral composed by Gérard Anthony, in 2004.\nThe Montana Mood Collection hit the shelves in 2006. It consists of 3 fragrances whose compositions are either floral (Montana Mood Sensual), chypre-floral (Montana Mood Sexy) or oriental-floral (Montana Mood Soft).\n2007 was the year of Parfum de Femme which was composed as oriental-floral perfume with prominent apple notes. A year later the French brand launched another floral-aquatic fragrance with the name Montana en Turquoise which is described as a beach scent for summer holiday. Montana 80, a floral-oriental scent with intense notes of milk, woods and tuberose and a retro feel was launched in 2010. Another men's fragrance was launched in 2011 - Graphite. Graphite is an oriental-spicy scent with woody and balmy notes.\nDesigner Montana has 31 perfumes in our fragrance base. The earliest edition was created in 1986 and the newest is from 2019. Montana fragrances were made in collaboration with perfumers Corinne Cachen, Olivia Jan, Nathalie Lorson, Francoise Caron, Antoine Lie, Annick Menardo, IFF, Edouard Flechier, Jean Guichard, Gerard Anthony, Max Gavarry, Emilie (Bevierre) Coppermann and Alexandra Carlin.",
