		title: "Jean Desprez",
		description:
			'Jean Desprez is a worldwide famous perfumer from France, great-grandson of perfumer F Millot. The only perfume so far produced by the house of Jean Desprez is Bal a Versailles, but the perfumer also designed fragrances independently, outside of the frames of the house. Jean Desprez was a first class perfumer who did not just follow trends, but invented them. His beautiful vintage classic perfumes were accompanied with outer packaging for his products designed by Paul Mergier and bottles designed by Leon Leyritz.\nSome of the fan of Desprez’ fragrance Bal a Versailles who used it or still use it are: Michael Jackson, Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth, Joan Collins, Elizabeth Taylor, Olivia de Havilland, Arlene Francis, Jackie Kennedy Onassis, Britt Ekland…\nBal a Versailles is view as the world’s most long-cherished and classically sensuous scent. The house of Jean Desprez designed it back in 1962 but it is still widely popular and used. Bal å Versailles belongs to the group of Floral Oriental fragrances and it is composed of more than 350 rare essences. Top notes of this perfume are rosemary, orange blossom, mandarin orange, cassia, jasmine, rose, neroli, bergamot, Bulgarian rose and lemon; middle notes are built around sandalwood, patchouli, lilac, orris root, vetiver, ylang-ylang and lily-of-the-valley; base notes rest on tolu balsam, amber, musk, benzoin, civet, vanilla, cedar and resins.\nThe first new fragrance of the house in 50 years was launched in 2002. That is a new version of the popular Bal a Versailles, combining a vintage classic with the needs of today. The new fragrance by Jean Desprez penetrates the psyche, arouses the senses, and seduces as well as comforts. The fragrance is very changeable and gives a different signal each time it is applied. It is a part of a new fragrance system that will keep the scent new and relevant for years to come. It retains the “sexy allure” of the past combined with a hint of independence.\nBefore founding the house of Jean Desprez, the perfumer designed several beautiful fragrances:\nAuguste Espirte de Chine Parfum was designed in 1925, as an homage to his grandfather, the perfumer Monsieur Millot. The perfume later became the most sought-after fragrance in Paris. Esprit de Chine opens with citruses, has a spicy, creamy floral heart, and closes with a base of white musk, tree moss and sandalwood.\nJean Desprez Escarmouche is a collectors fragrance poured in a sword-shaped bottle, with a Gold tip and cap (brass), black label, and a multi colored tassel.\nJean Desprez Debutante International Edition is an exquisite perfume created exclusively for Daggett & Ramsdell.\nJean Desprez Crepe de Chine was created by Jean Desprez in 1929 and based on exclusive, high-priced jasmine. It is one of the legendary complex French scents the production of which was discontinued because jasmine became too expensive.\nJean Desprez Votre Main Perfume was released in 1930, as one of the first Perfumes accompanied with a travel case with a laminated wood exterior with a grained interior combined with satin material.\nJean Desprez Jardanel Perfume was created in 1973 as a limited edition. It included a "sealed wax" top and satin lined box.\nJean Desprez 40 Love is one of the perfumer’s rare scents for both Men and Women. It is still sought after even today.\nJean Desprez has created some of the finest fragrances in the world:\n1917 Jardanel\n1939 Etourdissant\n1939 Grand Dame\n1939 Scheherazade\n1939 Votre Main\n1947 40 Love\n1962 Bal A Versailles\nDesigner Jean Desprez has 10 perfumes in our fragrance base. Jean Desprez is an old perfume house. The earliest edition was created in 1917 and the newest is from 1989. The nose who worked on the fragrances is Jean Desprez.',
