			'Ruhr-Universität Bochum, RUB, was the first in the world to produce its own scent in 2015. People who were involved in development and production of "Knowledge by RUB" were Perfume Researcher Prof. Dr. Dr. Dr. med. Hanns Hatt; Perfumeur Geza Schön, Berlin; Robert Müller-Grünow, Managing Director of "Scentcommunication"; Michael Mauer, whose Bochumer MM Duft UG acts as a sales partner for the RUB; RUB Rector Prof. Dr. Dr. Hc Elmarweiler and Dr. Oliver Pieper from the "Stadt-Parfümerie Pieper", which exclusively sells the scent at selected locations. "Not only in the nose are fragrance receptors, but also for example on sperm, in the intestine or in the skin. Fragrances regulate hormones and important messengers in the brain and thus influence physical and mental functions. Cineol, for example, has an invigorating effect because it activates not only the classic nerve cells, but also in high concentrations also the "warning nerves" trigeminal nerve. Geraniol, on the other hand, has a relaxing and powerful effect as it enhances the effect of inhibitory messengers in the brain. Together, the two fragrances form a toning combination, which increases mental performance. Further information on the effect and effects of five "Knowledge" components can be found in our collection." - a note from the brand.\nRUB is a new fragrance brand. Designer RUB has only one perfume in our fragrance encyclopedia from year 2015. The nose who worked on the fragrances is Geza Schoen.',
