		title: "Regina Schrecker",
		description:
			"Regina Schrecker began her career in the fashion industry as very young, working first as a model on the catwalks of Italy, before she tried out as an independent fashion designer of haute couture. Her collection was launched in 1980.\nShe designed an experimental line of knitwear, elegant prêt-à-porter, a unique collection of evening gowns and sophisticated fancy leather goods, a line of signature jeans and then moved on to wristwatches, ties, scarves, and sunglasses. She explored intimate wear and bathing suits and even home furnishings and décor.\nIn 1995, she received the prestigious Mela d’Oro from the Marisa Bellisario Foundation, a prize given to women who stand out for the inspiration and energy their success provides to Italian business. In 1990, she became the President of the Florence-Japan Association and had promoted a number of high-profile cultural events in collaboration with the City of Florence.\nIn 2000 she began costuming for a number of theatrical productions, the most important of which was perhaps a full operatic version of Madame Butterfly. In 2005, a line of junior clothing and bridal wear was also launched.\nIn 2007, she opened the “I Grandi della Moda” (Giants of Fashion) conference at the Rondò di Bacco Theater in Florence’s Palazzo Pitti.\nDesigner Regina Schrecker has only one perfume in our fragrance encyclopedia from year 1987.",
