			"Puredistance is an independent Perfume House that offers a truly exclusive collection of five Master Perfumes created in London, Paris and New York by renowned Master Perfumers. PUREDISTANCE is only available as Pure Perfume Extrait in perfume oil concentrations that vary between 25-32%. The noses behind the Puredistance Perfumes are Annie Buzantian in New York, Antoine Lie in Paris and Roja Dove in London. Three Master Perfumers who - inspired by the elegance of the Puredistance brand - have created a beautiful collection of perfumes. Puredistance launched its first perfume in 2007 and has quickly gained a strong following among true perfume lovers, almost entirely by word of mouth advertising. Currently customers can choose between five fragrances. Puredistance believes that top quality products need time to slowly 'grow', which is why a new Perfume is launched only once every one or two years. Additionally Puredistance creates various stylish accessories such as the metal and leather Perfume Sprayholders and Crystal Columns made by Swarovski. The main office and design center of PUREDISTANCE is located in the Netherlands. In a historical building a small creative team - guided by visionary founder Jan Ewoud Vos - designs and refines the artistic world of PUREDISTANCE. All Puredistance products consist of high quality ingredients and components and are assembled by hand with great care, passion and a strong eye for detail.\nDesigner Puredistance has 10 perfumes in our fragrance base. The earliest edition was created in 2007 and the newest is from 2019. Puredistance fragrances were made in collaboration with perfumers Antoine Lie, Annie Buzantian, Roja Dove and Cecile Zarokian.",
