		title: "Kate Moss",
		description:
			'Kate Moss is one of the world\'s top fashion models, helping popularize the "waif" look that dominated fashion advertising in the 1990s. Her relatively short stature in the modeling world (purportedly 5\' 7" or 168-172 cm) and her exceedingly slender figure were a sharp contrast to the taller, more curvaceous "super model" figures that dominated the late 1980s and early 1990s. Kate got her start as a model at age 16, and would go on to become one of the most in-demand print models whose appeal continues today, with a career spanning more than 20 years.\nKate Moss has modeled for top designers including Calvin Klein, Gucci, Dolce & Gabbana, Chanel and Bvlgari. She has been the face of cosmetics company Rimmel since 2005.\nIn 2007, Kate—always known as a tastemaker and credited for helping popularize such diverse trends as Ugg boots, skinny jeans, denim cut-offs and the "boho-chic" look—took a turn behind the scenes with a line of clothing produced for British retailer Topshop. Kate partnered with luxury leather goods producer Longchamp to launch a line of Kate Moss handbags, starting in 2010.\nKate\'s rock\'n\'roll lifestyle has been a popular subject for tabloids and the media. She has performed in recordings with Oasis, Primal Scream, Babyshambles and the Lemonheads. Kate has also appeared in a number of music videos for popular musicians such as The White Stripes and Elton John. Kate married Jamie Hince, the guitarist for rock band The Kills, in 2011.\nKate Moss partnered with Coty in 2007 to launch a fragrance under her name. The first fragrance, eponymous Kate Moss, was a tremendous success, and the partnership has to date produced nine other fragrances.\nDesigner Kate Moss has 10 perfumes in our fragrance base. The earliest edition was created in 2007 and the newest is from 2012. Kate Moss fragrances were made in collaboration with perfumers Nathalie Lorson, Alexis Dadier, Emilie (Bevierre) Coppermann and Shyamala Maisondieu.',
