			"Brooklyn Perfume Company is an independent perfume house founded by James Peterson. A chemist by training, Peterson traveled the world and eventually discovered his calling in French cuisine. After working in some of the finest French restaurants, he returned to the U.S. and opened Le Petit Robert in New York. From there, he shared his knowledge and skill as a professor at The French Culinary Institute and later became a celebrated culinary author. His first book, Sauces, was published in 1991 and won the James Beard Award for Cookbook of the Year. He has since published fifteen books and won more awards and acclaim, including a second James Beard award for Cooking in 2008.\nPeterson's fascination with cuisine eventually led him to the fragrance world, when a mention of ambergris in a 16th-century French culinary text led to experiments with aromatic substances. An olfactory sensualist, Peterson appreciates the subtleties of great wine, wonderful cuisine and fine fragrances. He established Brooklyn Perfume Company in 2015.\nBrooklyn Perfume Company is a new fragrance brand. Designer Brooklyn Perfume Company has 8 perfumes in our fragrance base all launched in 2015. The nose who worked on the fragrances is James Peterson.",
