			"Carlos Santana is the famous guitarist and rock, salsa and jazz musician born in 1947 in Mexico. He began his music career in San Francisco in 1960s, first as a solo musician, playing in jam sessions, and then as a part of the Santana Blues Band with David Brown and Gregg Rolie. The band soon adapted their front man’s name – Santana and became very popular, which lead to playing at Woodstock in 1969 and signing of the contract with Columbia Records.\nThe band changed its member through the years and released four albums (Santana had many side projects) before Carlos Santana obtained legal rights to the band's name and formed a new version of the band in 1973, changing style to jazz fusion. During the 70s and the 80s the band had many albums and their members kept on changing. Santana left Columbia Records in 1990 after twenty-two years and signed with Polygram.\nThe early 90s were not the best years for Santana. He ended up without a contract up until Arista Records’ Clive Davis, who had worked with Santana at Columbia Records, offered him a contract. The album “Supernatural” was born, featuring many young and popular artists such as Rob Thomas of Matchbox Twenty, Eric Clapton, Lauryn Hill, Wyclef Jean, Everlast, Cee-Lo, Maná, Dave Matthews, K. C. Porter, J. B. Eckl, etc. “Supernatural” reached number one on the US album charts and sold over 15 million copies in the United States, making it Santana's biggest sales success. The album won nine Grammy awards in 2000 and eight of them were won by Santana himself.\nIn 2002, Santana released the album “Shaman”, followed by “Possibilities” and “All That I Am” in 2005. “Guitar Heaven: The Greatest Guitar Classics of All Time” is his latest album and the 21st studio album by Santana band. It was released on 21st September 2010.\nVictory International company launched two fragrances with Carlos Santana’s name on them in 2005.\nDesigner Carlos Santana has 2 perfumes in our fragrance base all launched in 2005.",
