			"Lancaster is a cosmetics house founded in 1946. Their primary concern since then has been beauty and development of products to enhance and prolong natural beauty. The house has expanded through years and is now appreciated as a leading house in international luxury cosmetics and in the selective Sun care market. You can find Lancaster in over 40 countries and research centers in Europe and the USA. The company has developed with over 500 patents and incredible achievement in sun-exposure management and anti-ageing.\nThe mission of Lancaster has always been to be women’s companion through every stage of their lives. They strive to create innovative, honest, efficient and pleasing products that enable you to prolong and enhance youthful radiance. The house focuses on three fields of production: Skincare, Sun Care and Makeup. All products are characteristic for exceptional ingredients, futuristic technology and delicious textures. Lancaster is proud of their eye-catching mottos: The DNA of beauty, Visions of beauty, Innovation in motion and Pioneering science.\nThe history of Lancaster started when Georges Wurz, an industrialist and Lancaster pilot met Dr. Eugene Frezzati, a chemist specialized in cosmetics, in Monaco. They founded the company and the Lancaster factory in Monaco. The products that brought the first success were Crème Embryonnaire, Serum Tissulaire and le Lait pour les Mains, which made the brand famous throughout European countries, Asia and the Middle East.\nQuality of the products reached even Grace, the Princess of Monaco and Lancaster was appointed a sole supplier of beauty products for the palace. The house was incredibly innovative for the time and offered the line the Ligne Princiere based on anti-ageing products. In early 1970s the house launched their suncare products including pre-sun, sun protection, after sun, self tan and sun makeup. Lancaster was the first brand to apply the anti-ageing properties of Retinol in their skincare products.\nIn 1993 another ingredient was discovered to benefit the skin- oxygen. It was successfully applied in skin therapy vital Oxygen Supply. Soon after that, Lancaster started designing makeup lines to provide glamour. In 2002 patented RPF technology in Sun care protection was launched to combat free-radical damage.\nLancaster has specialized in sun expertise and has experience in safeguarding the skin and its DNA from UV rays, pollution and every form of aggression, and is also the only brand offering DNA action across all skincare and suncare products. They want to provide women with access to real science and high-performance skin & suncare products that preserve beauty and respect individual needs of each woman. Lancaster has entered the world of perfumery in 1979 and has launched 6 perfumes so far.\nDesigner Lancaster has 15 perfumes in our fragrance base. The earliest edition was created in 1977 and the newest is from 2019. Lancaster fragrances were made in collaboration with perfumers Emilie (Bevierre) Coppermann, Francis Kurkdjian, Christiane Plos, Sonia Constant and Marie Salamagne.",
